page.title: 07LIFE IN 1985.
page.content: Mrs. Lay gets up at 7.30. but sometimes 9.30.a.m. Mrs. Lay's life has differed since she and her husband retired from the surgery. Mrs. Lay's husband, Dr. E.T. Lay, was a doctor in the area for more than 30 years. She says that she has more free time to do things and persue her{hobbies.} Mrs. Lay has lots of hobbies like walking, gardening, knitting, sewing, attending to her animals but as little housework as possible. They have a boat and go to St. Anthony to fish. Mrs. Lay is a good cook but she only likes to cook savoury things. Mrs. Lay has four children. Mrs. Lay likes to go to the theatre but opportunities to see the professionals in this part of the country are limited.
